<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1865-05-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1865-05-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="916" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d916">
                    <head>Inhabitants of Balgach</head>
                    <dateline>
                        <placeName>Balgach</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1865-05-07">May 7, 1865</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <note rend="inline" rendition="#center" type="source">[Translation.]</note>
                    <p>At a public meeting held in the Lutheran church, in Balgach, at half-past ten
                        o’clock in the forenoon of the 7th of May, 1865, on a motion made by C.
                        Vulker, after the close of the polls for the district election, the
                        following resolution was unanimously adopted: <pb facs="0638" n="566" xml:id="pg_566"/>
                        <list>
                            <item>“The citizens of Balgach, at a meeting held on the 7th of May,
                                1865, unanimously resolved to ratify the address of sympathy and
                                condolence from the Swiss Confederation to the American Union, and
                                requested the authorities of the canton of St. Gall to make it known
                                to the proper persons.”</item>
                        </list>
                    </p>
                    <p>Adopted unanimously. The above abstract is correct.</p>
                    <closer>
                        <signed>
                            <list>
                                <item>S. OESCH, <hi rend="italic">President</hi>.</item>
                                <item>NÜNSCH, <hi rend="italic">Notary</hi>.</item>
                                <item>T. U. SONDEREGGER,</item>
                                <item>EDWARD WALTZLER, <hi rend="italic">Vote counters</hi>.</item>
                            </list>
                        </signed>
                    </closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>